Do not rely entirely on related functions for driving. Relevant functions are mainly designed for specific use scenarios such as highways and elevated roads, which require isolation zones and clear lane lines on the driving road, and meet other necessary operating conditions. If there are pedestrians or construction scenes, bad weather, or other operating conditions are not met, If satisfied, the relevant functions will be limited, and the driver needs to take over the vehicle immediately. The operation of related functions requires the support of assisted driving related components such as vehicle cameras, sensors, and positioning systems. Before turning on related functions, please ensure that the performance and operation of assisted driving related components are normal.
